html_attributions: 米珈琲 珈琲専科 自家焙煎
米珈琲 珈琲専科 自家焙煎

reviews.text: Terrible service. Terrible coffee. Premium prices. Interior decor is nice though, surrounded by village houses within a hidden street alley.

To be fair coffee is top notch but the price is also much more expensive than any other coffee shop in town.  There are plenty of house rules about how you should enjoy coffee in the shop but it does make people feel uncomfortable before stepping in.

If you want good coffee, yes this is the place. If you want good coffee while enjoying the time your own way, probably not.

They have the best hand drip coffee in town. The shopkeeper insists to bring out the uniqunes in every beans, by detailed roasting and dedication in brewing. You may have to be prepared that thr coffee here is not cheap but would be a good memory to try them out.
The staff here is very rude and impatient. disastrous.
Nice coffee
